        {
          "username": "Allison Robinson",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "108838634985771267557",
          "user_review_count": 151,
          "user_photo_count": 206,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWyD2c3AiFxpYYqyMI19zSys5C0e2Jukn5HWGz38-vD3rmCabJp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "I recently had a positive experience at this CVS pharmacy, despite the occasional long lines. Despite the wait times, I must say that the staff's professionalism and dedication to customer service truly shone through. The moment I walked in, I was greeted with a warm smile, and the staff members were quick to acknowledge the lines and assure customers that they were doing their best to expedite the process.\n\nWhat impressed me the most was the pharmacy team's ability to maintain a sense of calm and composure, even during peak hours. They efficiently multi tasked, addressing questions from multiple customers while still maintaining accuracy in dispensing medications. The staff also took the time to explain medications and offer advice, showing a genuine concern for their customers' well-being.\n\nDespite the long lines, I felt valued as a customer, and the staff's dedication to providing excellent service made the wait more bearable. CVS also offers a convenient online prescription refill service, which I found incredibly helpful to avoid the lines on busier days.\nSo overall while long lines can be a common occurrence at CVS, the exceptional customer service and professionalism of the staff more than make up for it. I appreciate their commitment to their customers' health and well-being, and I will continue to choose CVS for my pharmacy needs.",
